===Noun===
'''résumé''' (''plural'' '''[[résumés]]''')
#A [[summary]] or [[synopsis]].
#(''North America, Australia'') A [[curriculum vitae]]; an [[account]] of one's [[employment]] [[history]] and [[qualification]]s (often for presentation to a [[potential]] future [[employer]] when applying for a job.)

====Usage notes====
In the US ''résumé'' is commonly spelt ''[[resumé]]'', on the premise that the single accented version adheres to the long-time practice of accenting borrowed words to emphasize pronunciation, such as ''[[café]]'' and ''[[touché]]''. If submitting your summary in America to someone who is older, referring to it as your ''résumé'' may look odd to your prospective employer.  For younger employers, who have only ever seen it (perhaps incorrectly) auto-corrected by certain word-processing programs, ''resumé'' may seem better.

